cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.NE 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision tasks, specifically monocular depth estimation using convolutional neural networks (CNNs). Therefore, the most likely arXiv CS sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the challenges of memory and computing power requirements, which suggests that it may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of monocular depth estimation in robotics, which could place it in the cs.RO (Robotics) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes a novel approach to filter pruning, which could also place it in the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category.
